[[File:Xylophone.jpg|thumb|A xylophone]]
===Etymology===
From {{confix|en|xylo|t1=of wood|phone|t2=sound}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/ˈzaɪ.lə.ˌfəʊn/}}
* {{a|GA}} {{IPA|en|/ˈzaɪləˌfoʊn/}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-xylophone.ogg|Audio (GA)}}
* {{hyphenation|en|xy|lo|phone}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|musical instrument}} Any [[musical instrument]] ([[percussion idiophone]]) made of wooden slats graduated so as to make the sounds of the scale when struck with a small drumstick-like [[mallet]]; the standard Western [[concert xylophone]] or one of its derivatives.
#: {{ux|en|All I know how to play on my '''xylophone''' is "{{w|Mary Had a Little Lamb}}". Would you like to hear it?}}
